snippet.textDisplay: You fight the fever if the fever's out of control. Dangerously high (over 104F or 40C) or lasting more than 5 days. Otherwise, stay home and drink water - water helps your body regulate your temperature and just about everything else it does, too, so more gets used when you're sick. That's why "drink plenty of fluids" is ALWAYS on the list of self-care. If the fever itself isn't posing a danger, leave it alone, it's helping you.
